\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. D. gnidium} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 357 (1753). Erect, evergreen shrub up  to 200 cm; branches slender, straight, brown, uniformly leafy for  some distance below the apex; young shoots appressed-puberulent. Leaves 20-50 × 3-10 mm, glabrous, subcoriaceous, linear  to obovate-oblong, acute, glandular beneath. Flowers creamy-white, in small, terminal panicles. Hypanthium 2·5-4 mm, villous, slightly longer than the sepals. Drupe ovoid, red.{\i  S. Europe, mainly in the west, extending northwards to }47°{\i  N. in  W. France.} Al Bl Co Ga Gr Hs It ?Ju Lu Sa Si.
