\pard\f0\fs28  Plants from E. Greece (Evvoia) with large, acute, elliptical leaves have been distinguished as{\b  D. euboica} Rech. fil.,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr. }{\b 104}: 176 (1957). They differ strikingly from most specimens of {\i D. oleoides} from the Balkan peninsula, but can be exactly matched by specimens from E. Spain, where they intergrade with typical plants. 
